# Redesign Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
The current La Ruta Maya Station Prizes application uses a very simple, spreadsheet-like interface. The goal is to make it visually engaging and "fan-friendly" by applying modern web design aesthetics, utilizing existing brand imagery, and improving the presentation of the prize data. This will create a more premium, exciting experience for fans following the race.

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend Codebase
Summary: Overhaul the UI with vibrant coloring, modern typography, micro-animations, and a highly polished presentation.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Dev/La_Ruta_Maya/Station%20Pirzes/public/index.html)
- Add Google Fonts (e.g., 'Outfit' and 'Inter') to elevate typography.
- Transform the `<header>` into a visually striking 'Hero' section.
- Integrate the existing imagery ([larutamaya2026.webp](file:///c:/Dev/La_Ruta_Maya/Station%20Pirzes/public/larutamaya2026.webp) logo and [Belikin-wordpress-image-838x471.webp](file:///c:/Dev/La_Ruta_Maya/Station%20Pirzes/public/Belikin-wordpress-image-838x471.webp) as background/banner elements).
- Add container structures to allow for better responsive styling.

#### [MODIFY] [styles.css](file:///c:/Dev/La_Ruta_Maya/Station%20Pirzes/public/styles.css)
- Define a modern, tropical/Belikin-inspired color palette (rich greens, gold/yellows, tropical cyans, and deep contrast colors).
- Replace the bare table look with a polished, glassmorphism-inspired or softly shadowed card design.
- Style the tabs as vibrant "pills" that look clickable and reactive.
- Add CSS animations (e.g., smooth fade-ins and slide-ups for table rows, hover effects).
- Highlight "Winner" rows dramatically (using gold accents or subtle glow effects) so they stand out like true champions.

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Dev/La_Ruta_Maya/Station%20Pirzes/public/app.js)
- Inject animation delays into dynamically rendered rows so they cascade in smoothly (staggered entrance).
- Potentially add icons (like a 🏆 emoji or SVG) automatically to winner rows.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Local Tests
- Run the server locally using `npm start` (which runs `node server.js`).
- Use the `browser_subagent` to navigate to `http://localhost:3000` (or the configured port) and capture a screenshot/video of the new animated UI.

### Manual Verification
- The user can review the browser subagent recording.
- The user can deploy the changes to Vercel and view the updated live site to ensure the aesthetics meet their expectations.
